			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Any human bards?<a name="23805"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 11:42 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>When I started the game I made a human Bard worshipping Bristlebane and have had a ball with him.  Even though I got my hands on a spectacularly bad old Prima guide and actually put 15 points into Wisdom I've managed to flourish.
<br />

<br />
There are just so many stats boosting items in the game these days that your starting stats are pretty irrelavent once you can start making a little money hunting goblins in Butcherblock.  And when you can start Chant or Charm Kiting Hill Giants in Rathe Mountains:)?  No money worries by then.
<br />

<br />
As far as Stamina goes, yes it's nice to have the extra hit points in the end game but, even for Warriors, extra stamina will only add 300-400 hp.  I really don't think it's a good investment for a Bard.
<br />

<br />
If you're on an older server and have a good supply of cheap Strength boosting items for sale in the bazaar I'd go for 15 Dex and 10 Charisma as a human.  If you're on a new server I'd suggest 15 Strength and 10 Charisma and be sure to do the Qeynos newbie armor quest instead of the Freeport as Qeynos newbie armor is Dexterity heavy.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
