				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Any human bards?<a name="24231"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 27 04 8:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My bard is human. And agnostic to boot! I didn't give a hoot about the imbued armours when I created my bard. I wanted to be free to move about the old world and explore all the quests and places where my iksar necro couldn't go. And I really like being able to use the OT hammer without being KOS at the port in spot (not a big deal, but it came as an added bonus).
<br />

<br />
I never quite understood about the complaints about humans being nightblind... My first character I played past level 30 was a human ranger, and he was my main for a long time. I never had any problems with night or dark places. Granted, you had to have a light source, but they're way common and one inventory space wasn't too bad until I could find a worn item for a light source.
<br />

<br />
Starting stats for bards make no difference to me. The variance is so small. After that, like with my ranger before, there was really no choice. All elves look wimpy and have this unsecure schoolboy look about them, and do you REALLY want to have a cat singing all day long? No choice there, human is the way to go <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
