				<td colspan="2"><span>Hmmm, having played a night blind and an  infravision character both, I can tell you that light sources (for me) never make up for infravision. 
<br />

<br />
90% of the time its only a minor inconvenience, but sometimes, like on a night swarm kite,  or pulling dark rooms, it can be a bit more than a little inconvenient.
<br />

<br />
Yeah, you can fairly easily work around it, but it was a single factor in the old character creation screens that made your character go from 'low difficulty' to 'med difficulty'.
<br />

<br />
Still, making sure you have a light source often requires you to select an item for is light capabilities and not other, perhaps more usefull stats. 
<br />

<br />
I still made another human pc after the first one, so obviously it didn't bother me that much.
<br />

